G. Reinsel
dcterms:description: The gas furnace process involves mixing air and methane to create a gas mixture containing carbon dioxide. The control input is methane gas, and the output is the CO2 concentration. The dataset consists of 296 successive pairs of input and output data, with 200 samples used for training and 96 for testing.
dcterms:title: Gas Furnace Process

dcterms:creator: J. Schoukens
J. Suykens
L. Ljung
dcterms:description: The Wiener-Hammerstein system consists of a static nonlinear part surrounded by two dynamic linear systems. The dataset includes 188,000 input/output pairs, with 100,000 samples for training and 88,000 for testing.
dcterms:title: Wiener-Hammerstein System
